data.name: Evonik
data.description:
Our purpose is the cornerstone of our performance pledge: “Leading beyond chemistry to improve life, today and tomorrow.” It can be traced back to our company’s roots and describes why we do something, what drives us and the contribution Evonik makes to society over and above generating profits.

At Evonik, we go beyond chemistry to make life a little better day in, day out – a goal we are committed to. We aim to have a direct, positive impact on everyone’s life by enhancing the properties of our customers’ products. Our purpose is hence the driving force behind our strategic decisions, through which we naturally take responsibility for the present and future generations.

data.name: AEROSIL
data.description: Evonik is the inventor of AEROSIL® fumed silica, which is a synthetic fumed silica that is produced by flame hydrolysis. For over 70 years AEROSIL® has proven to enhance performance in many markets and applications. Today Evonik's AEROSIL® portfolio covers a broad range of surface areas, as well as very different surface chemistries. Also, AEROSIL® does not get tired in finding new markets, applications and effects. AEROSIL® is invented to improve.

data.name: HyaCare®
data.description: Hyaluronic acid solutions with superior age-defying and moisturization efficacy.

data.name: VISIOMER
data.description:
VISIOMER® Specialty Methacrylates offer an innovative way to customize product properties for various end use applications.
With a range of alkyl/aryl (meth)acrylates, aminofunctional monomers, methacrylamides, ether methacrylates, crosslinkers, HEMA for contact lenses, wet adhesion monomers and specialty intermediates, VISIOMER® has become a trusted partner in designing customized products to meet specific needs.

data.name: SIPERNAT
data.description: Evonik's SIPERNAT® precipitated silicas are well-known and used as an anti-caking agent, carrier, stabilizer, defoamer, rheology controller, microplastic replacement, and numerous others. The SIPERNAT® product range provides a specialized product solution for many challenges. Through advanced product technology, custom application development and best-in-class handling expertise, Evonik's technical team supports customers in finding the right solution to step up the performance.

data.name: ZEOFREE
data.description: Evonik's ZEOFREE® precipitated silicas are well-known and used as an anti-caking agent, carrier, stabilizer, defoamer, rheology controller, microplastic replacement, and numerous others. The ZEOFREE®product range provides a specialized product solution for many challenges. Through advanced product technology, custom application development and best-in-class handling expertise, Evonik's technical team supports customers in finding the right solution to step up the performance.

data.name: BeautiFerm
data.description: Formulate natural skincare products that leverage the powerful, rejuvenating benefits of fermented beauty actives with BeautiFerm. From restoring a youthful glow to visibly firming skin and boosting its regeneration, these natural, sustainable, and scientifically proven ingredients are ideal additions to creams, lotions, and other anti-aging solutions popular amongst today's skintellectual consumers.

data.name: AEROSIL® 130
data.description: AEROSIL® 130 is a fumed silica with a high specific surface area, making it an excellent thickening and reinforcing agent for a wide range of applications. This product is particularly well-suited for use in adhesives, coatings, and composites, as it can improve mechanical strength and increase the durability of the final product. AEROSIL® 130 is a hydrophilic fumed silica with a specific surface area of 130 m2/g.

data.name: SK-Influx® MB
data.description: SK-Influx® is a skin-identical lipid concentrate for enhanced skin moisturization and protection. It is ideal for aging skin, dry skin and sensitive skin. SK-Influx® is a concentrated formulation, consisting of a multi-lamellar (membrane) system resembling the structure of the lipid barrier in the Stratum Corneum. It is a concentrated mix of different types of ceramides, cholesterol, free fatty acids and phytosphingosine makes it an ideal ingredient for personal care products with unique restoring capabilities.

data.name: BeautiFerm® Resurf L PG
data.description: BeautiFerm® Resurf L PG is a fermented ingredient carefully selected from lactic acid bacterium (LAB). It strengthens the microbial shield by promoting the growth of beneficial microbes on the skin, driven by probiotic science. This product supports a balanced and healthy skin microbiota. It comes in liquid form and is preserved with pentylene glycol.

data.name: SIPERNAT® 9000 PC
data.description: SIPERNAT® 9000 PC is composed of exceptionally sturdy, round-edged hydrated silica particles and is therefore the preferred choice for formulations with a long-lasting scrubbing effect. The large SIPERNAT® 9000 PC particles are the preferred choice for strong desquamation or as a sensory indicator when combined with smaller particles for cleaning.

data.name: AEROSIL® R 812 S
data.description: AEROSIL® R 812 S is hydrophobic fumed silica grade treated with HMDS (Hexamethyldisilazane). It is even more hydrophobic than AEROSIL® R 812 and convenient for stabilizing a defoamer and well suitable as a component of foam control agents.

data.name: SIPERNAT® 50 S
data.description: SIPERNAT® 50 S is a hydrophilic, finely milled silica. Besides its application as flow aid and highly effective anticaking agent it also may serve as carrier of especially high absorptive capacity in case particle fineness is required.

data.name: ROHACELL® IG-F
data.description: ROHACELL® IG-F structural foam is a closed-cell rigid foam crafted using polymethacrylimide (PMI) chemistry and is entirely free of CFCs. As an "industrial grade" foam, ROHACELL® IG-F represents the standard product within their range of rigid foam offerings. This versatile foam is well-suited for a diverse range of applications in sectors such as automotive, medical, and various industrial applications, making it a reliable choice for a broad array of purposes.

data.name: ROHACELL® WF
data.description: ROHACELL® WF is a core material with a coarse cell size that offers exceptional heat resistance and creep compression strength. It is characterized by its high temperature and compressive resistance, making it suitable for various applications, including aircraft, space, automotive, industrial, and radomes.

data.name: ROHACELL® A
data.description: ROHACELL® A is a closed-cell rigid foam crafted from polymethacrylimide (PMI) chemistry. Notably, it is entirely devoid of CFCs, aligning with environmental considerations. Engineered with precision, ROHACELL® A foam is tailored to meet the rigorous standards of the aerospace industry. It offers versatility in aerospace applications, supporting both prepreg processing and vacuum infusion across various pressure and temperature ranges.

data.name: VISIOMER® EHMA
data.description: VISIOMER® EHMA (2-Ethylhexyl methacrylate) is a hydrophobic monomer with a low glass transition temperature (Tg), minimal shrinkage, and low viscosity. This monomer offers flexibility and exhibits excellent dilution and solvency power. It is widely used in the production of various polymers for diverse applications across industries such as adhesives and sealants, coatings, oil and gas, personal care, and healthcare. Its unique properties make it a valuable component in the formulation of materials that require flexibility, low shrinkage, and efficient solvency capabilities.

data.name: VISIOMER® IDMA

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Bisomer IDMA, Light Ester ID, Methacrylic acid, isodecyl ester, SR 242, Visiomer IDMA

data.description: VISIOMER® IDMA (Isodecyl methacrylate) is a hydrophobic monomer known for its low shrinkage and low glass transition temperature (Tg). It exhibits excellent dilution power, resulting in low viscosity when used in polymer formulations. The low Tg of IDMA imparts extreme softness to the resulting polymers. This versatile monomer finds applications in various industries including adhesives and sealants, coatings, oil and gas, personal care, healthcare, and textile and leather.

data.name: VISIOMER® Terra C13-MA
data.description: VISIOMER® Terra C13-MA (methacrylic ester 13.0) is a specialty monomer that offers enhanced water repellency and improved resistance against polar solvents. It is commonly employed to increase the hydrophobicity of resins, making them more resistant to water and other polar substances. This particular monomer is derived from raw materials obtained from natural oils, highlighting its environmentally friendly nature. VISIOMER® Terra C13-MA finds applications in various industries including adhesives and sealants, coatings, construction, oil and gas, paper, personal care, and healthcare.

data.name: VISIOMER® Terra C17,4-MA
data.description: VISIOMER® Terra C17,4-MA (methacrylic ester 17.4) is a methacrylate monomer with a long alkyl chain, resulting in a low glass transition temperature (Tg). This monomer is commonly used to enhance the hydrophobicity of resins, making them more resistant to water and other polar substances. In addition to its role as a hydrophobicity enhancer, VISIOMER® Terra C17,4-MA is also employed as a flexibilizer and internal plasticizer in coatings and reactive resins applications. By incorporating this monomer into formulations, manufacturers can achieve improved flexibility and enhanced performance of their coatings and reactive resins.

data.name: VISIOMER® c-HMA
data.description: VISIOMER® c-HMA (Cyclohexyl methacrylate) is a cycloaliphatic monomer characterized by its low viscosity. It serves as a fundamental component in the formulation of polymers that exhibit excellent weathering resistance and chemical resistance. This monomer is widely utilized in industries such as adhesives, sealants, coatings, and composites to enhance the performance and durability of the resulting products. By incorporating VISIOMER® c-HMA, manufacturers can develop polymers with superior resistance to environmental factors and various chemicals, ensuring long-lasting and reliable applications in diverse settings.

data.name: VISIOMER® IBOA
data.description: VISIOMER® IBOA (isobornyl acrylate) is a monofunctional acrylate monomer known for its good reactivity and high glass transition temperature. It finds application in the reduction of viscosity within UV/EB curing formulations. This versatile compound is widely employed in the adhesives and sealants industry.

data.name: VISIOMER® Terra IBOMA
data.description: VISIOMER® Terra IBOMA is a bulky side-chain alkyl methacrylate monomer known for its exceptionally high glass transition temperature (Tg). It offers the advantage of lowering viscosity in polymers, enabling the formulation of high solids content. This monomer finds applications in various industries, including adhesives and sealants, coatings, and composites.

data.name: VISIOMER® BNMA

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Benzyl 2-methyl-2-propenoate, Benzyl 2-methylacrylate, Benzyl α-methylacrylate, NSC 20970, Phenylmethyl 2-methyl-2-propenoate

data.description: VISIOMER® BNMA (benzyl methacrylate) is an aromatic monofunctional methacrylate known for its low viscosity. It serves as a reactive diluent, offering excellent solvency in adhesive, ink, and coating formulations. This versatile compound finds applications in various industries, including adhesives and sealants, coatings, composites, and electronics.

data.name: VISIOMER® AMA
data.description: VISIOMER® AMA (allyl methacrylate) showcases exceptional performance due to its two double bonds with different reactivity, enabling graft copolymerization in emulsions. It serves as a crosslinker and co-monomer for graft polymers and serves as a base product for the production of silanes. This versatile compound finds application in industries such as intermediates for synthesis, as well as plastics.

data.name: VISIOMER® EGDMA

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 1,2-Bis(Methacryloyloxy)ethane, 1,2-Ethanediol Dimethacrylate, 2-(Methacryloyloxy)ethyl 2-methylacrylate, 2-methyl-2-propenoic acid 1,2-ethanediyl ester, Ethyldiol Methacrylate, Ethylene Glycol Bis(Methacrylate), Methacrylic Acid Ethylene Ester

data.description: VISIOMER® EGDMA (ethylene glycol dimethacrylate) is a hydrophilic dimethacrylate monomer renowned for its low viscosity. It is an excellent choice as a crosslinking agent, effectively enhancing the resistance properties of polymers and elastomers. This versatile compound finds applications in various industries, including 3D printing, adhesives and sealants, coatings, construction, personal care, and healthcare, as well as plastics and rubber.

data.name: VISIOMER® TRGDMA
data.description: VISIOMER® TRGDMA (triethylene glycol dimethacrylate) is a dimethacrylate monomer with low viscosity, making it well-suited for use as a crosslinking agent in free radical polymerization. Additionally, it serves as an adhesion promoter and hardener for PVC plastisols, as well as a component in reactive resins. This versatile compound finds applications in a wide range of industries, including 3D printing, adhesives and sealants, coatings, construction, personal care, and healthcare, as well as plastics and rubber.

data.name: VISIOMER® PEG 200 DMA

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Heneicosaethylene glycol dimethacrylate, Oligoethylene glycol dimethacrylate, Poly(ethylene oxide) dimethacrylate, Polyethylene glycol dimethacrylate, Polyethylene glycol methacrylate, Polyoxyethylene dimethacrylate

data.description: VISIOMER® PEG 200 DMA (polyethylene glycol 200 dimethacrylate) is an aliphatic dimethacrylate monomer with low viscosity, making it an excellent choice as a co-monomer to enhance the mechanical properties and chemical resistance of resins. This label-free monomer finds applications in a variety of industries, including 3D printing, adhesives and sealants, coatings, composites, construction and, personal care.

data.name: VISIOMER® PEG 8000 DMA W

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Heneicosaethylene glycol dimethacrylate, Oligoethylene glycol dimethacrylate, Poly(ethylene oxide) dimethacrylate, Polyethylene glycol dimethacrylate, Polyethylene glycol methacrylate, Polyoxyethylene dimethacrylate

data.description: VISIOMER® PEG 8000 DMA W (polyethylene glycol 8000 dimethacrylate) is a long-chain hydrophilic crosslinking monomer. It is commonly utilized as a co-monomer in formulations for joint sealants, specifically to seal construction gaps in concrete slabs, decks, and similar structures. This particular compound finds applications in the adhesives and sealants, coatings, and construction industries.

data.name: VISIOMER® 1,3-BDDMA
data.description: VISIOMER® 1,3-BDDMA (1,3-butanediol dimethacrylate) is a dimethacrylate monomer with low viscosity. It is well-suited for use as a crosslinking agent, providing cohesive strength to polymers. This versatile compound finds applications in various industries, including adhesives and sealants, composites, construction, as well as plastics and rubber.

data.name: VISIOMER® 1,4-BDDMA
data.description: VISIOMER® 1,4-BDDMA is a low viscosity dimethacrylate monomer widely used as a crosslinker. It serves as an excellent replacement for styrene in composite resin, functioning as an adhesion promoter and a hardener for PVC plastisols. Additionally, it acts as a coagent for peroxide crosslinking of elastomers. This versatile compound finds applications in industries such as adhesives and sealants, composites, construction, and plastics and rubber.

data.name: VISIOMER® 1,6-HDDMA
data.description: VISIOMER® 1,6-HDDMA (1,6-hexanediol dimethacrylate) is a hydrophobic dimethacrylate monomer highly suitable as a crosslinker for reactive systems. This versatile monomer finds applications in industries such as 3D printing, adhesives and sealants, coatings, as well as plastics and rubber.

data.name: VISIOMER® GDMA
data.description: VISIOMER® GDMA (1,3-glycerol dimethacrylate) is a hydrophilic dimethacrylate monomer specifically utilized as a crosslinker in adhesive and sealant formulations. It offers efficient adhesion properties, thanks to its additional OH functionality. This versatile monomer finds applications in the adhesives and sealants, as well as coatings industry.

data.name: VISIOMER® TMPTMA
data.description: VISIOMER® TMPTMA (trimethylol propane trimethacrylate) is a trifunctional methacrylate monomer renowned for its ability to serve as a crosslinking agent. It imparts cohesive strength and high temperature resistance to polymers and elastomers by forming dense networks. This versatile monomer finds applications in industries such as 3D printing, adhesives and sealants, coatings, construction, as well as plastics and rubber.

data.name: VISIOMER® HEMATMDI
data.description: VISIOMER® HEMATMDI (diurethane dimethacrylate) is a difunctional methacrylate monomer featuring a urethane group. It is characterized by its low volatility and high reactivity. This compound finds extensive use in radiation curing formulations for varnishes, inks, adhesives, as well as dental compounds. Industries such as 3D printing, adhesives and sealants, coatings, personal care, and healthcare benefit from its versatile properties.

data.name: VISIOMER® ETMA
data.description: VISIOMER® ETMA (ethyltriglycol methacrylate) is a hydrophilic methacrylate monomer known for its ability to enhance adhesion, flexibility, and minimize shrinkage in polymers. It exhibits low volatility and serves as a reactive diluent in reactive systems. This versatile compound finds applications in industries such as adhesives and sealants, as well as coatings.

data.name: VISIOMER® THFMA
data.description: VISIOMER® THFMA is a low viscosity and low odor monomethacrylate monomer that significantly enhances flexibility and adhesion in adhesive applications. Its low volatility makes it suitable as a reactive diluent for reactive systems, particularly in adhesives. Industries such as adhesives and sealants, coatings, and construction benefit from the diverse applications of VISIOMER® THFMA.

data.name: VISIOMER® BDGMA
data.description: VISIOMER® BDGMA (butyl diglycol methacrylate) is a monofunctional and label-free methacrylate monomer that contains ether functionality. It possesses a very low glass transition temperature (Tg), making it an excellent plasticizing monomer. This compound is utilized in the formulation of polymers, copolymers, and light-curing systems. Industries such as adhesives and sealants, coatings, and construction benefit from the versatile properties of VISIOMER® BDGMA.

data.name: VISIOMER® C18 PEG 1105 MA W
data.description: VISIOMER® C18 PEG 1105 MA W is a polar methacrylate monomer in water and GMAA, consisting of a hydrophilic polyethylene glycol side chain with a C16-C18 hydrophobic tail. This monomer is well-suited for use as an associative polymeric thickener in emulsion polymers. Industries such as coatings, healthcare, oil and gas, paper, personal care, and water treatment can benefit from its properties.

data.name: VISIOMER® MPEG 500 MA
data.description: VISIOMER® MPEG 500 MA is a pure and water-free methoxy polyethylene glycol methacrylate monomer, available in liquid form for easy handling. It is soluble in water and consists of approximately 12 ethylene oxide (EO) units in its chain. Industries such as coatings, healthcare, and personal care can utilize this monomer for various applications.

data.name: VISIOMER® MPEG 750 MA W
data.description: VISIOMER® MPEG 750 MA W is a highly polar monomer with excellent water solubility. It is composed of methoxy polyethylene glycol 750 methacrylate, with a concentration of 50% in water. This monomer is commonly used as a co-polymerizable emulsifier to stabilize latex polymer systems, particularly emulsions. Industries such as coatings, oil and gas, personal care, and pharma and healthcare can benefit from its properties.

data.name: VISIOMER® MPEG 1005 MA W
data.description: VISIOMER® MPEG 1005 MA W is a highly polar monomer with excellent water solubility. It consists of methoxy polyethylene glycol 1000 methacrylate, with a concentration of 50% in water. This monomer finds applications in industries such as construction, oil and gas, and personal care.

data.name: VISIOMER® MPEG 2005 MA W
data.description: VISIOMER® MPEG 2005 MA W is a highly polar monomer with excellent water solubility. It consists of methoxy polyethylene glycol 2000 methacrylate, with a concentration of 50% in water. This monomer finds applications in industries such as construction, oil and gas, and personal care.

data.name: VISIOMER® MPEG 5005 MA W
data.description: VISIOMER® MPEG 5005 MA W is a highly polar monomer with excellent water solubility. It consists of methoxy polyethylene glycol 5000 methacrylate, with a concentration of 50% in water. This monomer finds applications in various industries including coatings, adhesives, composites, construction, plastics, textiles, leather, oil & gas, paper, water, personal care, health care, and synthesis.

data.name: VISIOMER® HEMA-P 70 M
data.description: VISIOMER® HEMA-P 70 M is a monofunctional methacrylate with a phosphate group in the side chain. It is supplied in 30% methyl methacrylate, which gives it a low viscosity and makes it easy to handle. This monomer provides superior adhesion to polar surfaces such as metals, glass, ceramics, and concrete. In direct-to-metal coatings, it enhances corrosion resistance and improves film strength. Visiomer® HEMA-P 70M can be used as a functional co-monomer in acrylic emulsions for coating resins, as well as an adhesion promoter in adhesive formulations.

data.name: VISIOMER® HEMA-P 100
data.description: VISIOMER® HEMA-P 100 is a monofunctional methacrylate with a phosphate group in the side chain. It enables superior adhesion to polar surfaces such as metals, glass, ceramics, and concrete. In direct-to-metal coatings, it enhances corrosion resistance and improves film strength. This monomer can be used as a functional co-monomer in acrylic emulsions for coating resins, as a reactive co-diluent in composite resins, or as an adhesion promoter in adhesive formulations.

data.name: VISIOMER® MADAME
data.description: VISIOMER® MADAME is a monofunctional methacrylate with a tertiary amino group in the side chain. It is an ideal ingredient for improving the adhesion of formulations. This monomer is widely used in the preparation of cationic polymers, particularly quaternary ammonium polymers and flocculants. Industries such as coatings, oil and gas, paper, and personal care can benefit from the unique properties of VISIOMER® MADAME.

data.name: VISIOMER® DMAPMA
data.description: VISIOMER® DMAPMA (3-Dimethylamino propyl methacrylamide) is an amino functional methacrylamide monomer. Its methacrylamide structure provides increased hydrolytic stability compared to methacrylic esters. This monomer is commonly used to enhance pigment wetting and improve substrate adhesion to polymers. Industries such as coatings, oil and gas, paper, personal care, and healthcare can benefit from the unique properties of VISIOMER® DMAPMA.

data.name: VISIOMER® TMAEMC
data.description: VISIOMER® TMAEMC (2-Trimethylammoniumethyl methacrylate chloride - aqueous solution-) is a quaternized aminofunctional monomer specifically designed for the preparation of water-soluble cationic polymers. It finds applications in various industries such as oil and gas, paper, personal care, pharmaceuticals and healthcare, and water treatment. By utilizing VISIOMER® TMAEMC, polymers with desirable cationic properties can be created, offering benefits in areas such as emulsion stabilization, flocculation, and antimicrobial activity.

data.name: VISIOMER® MAPTAC
data.description: VISIOMER® MAPTAC (3-Trimethylammoniumpropyl methacrylamide chloride - aqueous solution-) is a quaternized aminofunctional monomer specifically designed for the preparation of water-soluble cationic polymers. It finds applications in various industries including adhesives and sealants, oil and gas, paper, personal care, pharmaceuticals, and healthcare. By utilizing VISIOMER® MAPTAC, water-soluble cationic polymers can be synthesized, offering advantages such as enhanced adhesion, and flocculation. This versatile monomer contributes to the development of innovative products in a wide range of applications.

data.name: VISIOMER® MEEU 50 W
data.description: VISIOMER® MEEU 50 W is a water-based solution containing 50% ureido methacrylate. This product is specifically formulated to enhance the wet adhesion properties of emulsion polymers and improve the wet scrub resistance of the final products. It finds applications in industries such as adhesives and sealants, coatings, and textile and leather. By incorporating VISIOMER® MEEU 50 W into formulations, manufacturers can achieve improved performance and durability in their products, particularly in wet conditions.

data.name: VISIOMER® MEEU 25 M
data.description: VISIOMER® MEEU 25 M is an ureido methacrylate solution containing 25% ureido methacrylate in MMA (methyl methacrylate). It is specifically designed for enhancing wet adhesion and wet scrub resistance in various polymer applications. This versatile product finds utility in industries such as adhesives and sealants, coatings, as well as textile and leather. VISIOMER® MEEU 25 M provides improved performance in terms of adhesion and durability, making it a valuable additive for achieving high-quality results in polymer formulations.

data.name: Evonik
data.description:
Our purpose is the cornerstone of our performance pledge: “Leading beyond chemistry to improve life, today and tomorrow.” It can be traced back to our company’s roots and describes why we do something, what drives us and the contribution Evonik makes to society over and above generating profits.

At Evonik, we go beyond chemistry to make life a little better day in, day out – a goal we are committed to. We aim to have a direct, positive impact on everyone’s life by enhancing the properties of our customers’ products. Our purpose is hence the driving force behind our strategic decisions, through which we naturally take responsibility for the present and future generations.
